\begin{document}$$ {\text{MT}} = a + b \times {\text{ID}}; $$\end{document}where MT is movement time, ID is the index of difficulty, and a and b are empirical constants. The critical variable is the ID, which relates the amplitude (A) of the movement to the width (W) of the targets. It is expressed as:\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
